{{Designation list | designation1 = Ramsar | designation1_offname = Le Cesine | designation1_date = 6 December 1977 | designation1_number = 168<ref>{{Cite web|title=Le Cesine|website=[[Ramsar Convention|Ramsar]] Sites Information Service|url=https://rsis.ramsar.org/ris/168|accessdate=25 April 2018}}</ref>}} The oasis of '''Le Cesine''' is a [[wetland]] and natural state reserve extending for 380 hectares near [[Lecce]], in southern [[Italy]]. It has been recognized as one of the [[Ramsar Convention|Ramsar]] wetland sites of international importance in 1977, and a state nature reserve and a special protection area – SPA ([[Birds Directive]]) in 1980.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ec.europa.eu/environment/life/project/Projects/index.cfm?fuseaction=search.dspPage&n_proj_id=61|title=Cesine - Conservation of Wetlands in Cesine and decrease of human impact in the area|last=|first=|date=|website=Europa.eu|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=27 August 2017}}</ref> The management of the oasis has been entrusted to [[World Wide Fund for Nature|WWF]] Italy by the Ministry of the Environment and has been managed by WWF since 1979.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.wwf.it/oasi/puglia/le_cesine/le_cesine__english_version_.cfm|title=Le Cesine (english version)|access-date=27 August 2017|language=it}}</ref>
