[[File:ValleFassaposizione.png|thumb|Location of the Fascia Valley (red box) in Trentino]] The '''Fassa Valley''' ([[Ladin language|Ladin]]: ''Val de Fascia'', {{lang-it|Val di Fassa}}, {{lang-de|Fassatal}}) is a valley in the [[Dolomites]] in [[Trentino]], northern [[Italy]]. As an administrative valley community (Italian: ''Comunità di valle'', German: ''Talgemeinschaft'') of Trentino, it is called ''Region Comun General de Fascia''.
The valley is the home of the [[Ladin people|Ladin community]] in Trentino, which make up the majority of the population.
==Municipalities== The municipalities in the valley include (''Ladin name''):
*[[Canazei]] (''Cianacèi'') *[[Campitello di Fassa|Campitello]] (''Ciampedèl'') *[[Mazzin]] (''Mazin'') *[[Sèn Jan di Fassa]] *[[Soraga]] (Sorega) *[[Moena]] (''Moéna'')
==External links== *{{Commonscat-inline|Val di Fassa}} *{{wikivoyage-inline|Fassa Valley}}
