[[File:Gelderland-Flag.svg|thumb|right|250px|Flag of Gelderland (ratio 9:13; de facto 2:3)]]

The '''flag of [[Gelderland]]''' is a horizontal tricolour of [[blue]], [[yellow]] (''gold'') and [[black]]. The flag was determined on 15 April 1953 by the Provinciale Staten. Its colours originate from the coat of arms of Gelderland which in turn was based on the coat of arms of the [[Guelders|Hertogdom Gelre]].[[File:Guelders-Jülich Arms.svg|thumb|right|150px|Coat of arms of Gelre (1379)]]

