[[File:Penshaw from Herrington Park.jpg|left|thumb|250px|Herrington Country Park, looking towards [[Penshaw Monument]].]]

'''Herrington Country Park''' is a park and open public space in [[Sunderland]], [[Tyne and Wear]]. Located adjacent to [[Penshaw Monument]], the park  was built on the site of a former colliery. The park has developed into a significant home for wildlife, hosting up to 100 species of birds.<ref>{{Cite web|URL=http://www.picturesofengland.com/England/Tyne_&_Wear/Houghton_le_Spring/Herrington_Country_Park/history|title=History of Herrington Country Park
|website=PicturesofEngland.com|access-date=2017-12-24}}</ref>

The Park has hosted several major events, including BBC Radio One's Big Weekend in 2005, with [[Gwen Stefani]], [[Foo Fighters]] and the [[Black Eyed Peas]]<ref>{{Cite web|URL=http://www.bbc.co.uk/pressoffice/pressreleases/stories/2005/04_april/19/radio1.shtml|title=Sunderland Home Page - Sunderland City Council|website=BBC Radio One|access-date=2017-12-24}}</ref>, as well as an Olympic Torch Relay in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|URL=http://www.bbc.co.uk/pressoffice/pressreleases/stories/2005/04_april/19/radio1.shtml|title=Weekend of Fire and Water as thousands welcome the Olympic Torch in Sunderland and Durham|website=Sunderland Echo|access-date=2017-12-24}}</ref>

